other_tests.findings: Fat stranding is present about a dilated appendix, consistent with appendicitis. There is marked pericecal inflammation. Enlarged mesenteric lymph nodes are present, also stable compared to prior. No evidence of free air or fluid collection.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Similar appearance to prior study without any evidence of macroscopic free air or fluid collection; enlarged mesenteric lymph nodes stable compared to prior.
